Concepts Learned during this clonign assignments are:
1. CSS Syntax - Properties, Values, 
2. Inline vs Block - An inline element does not start on a new line. 
An inline element only takes up as much width as necessary. 
while A block-level element always starts on a new line and takes up the full width available
3. Margins - used to create space around elements
4. Padding - used to create space around an element's content
5. Borders
6. Divs 
7. Classes
8. Centering - Centering lines of text, Centering a block of text or an image
9. Flexbox - to create a row or a column axis layout
